“The reason why Naxalites have been able to sustain their insurgency for so
long is due to three main reasons: the absence or failure of governance; the
romanticism and propaganda of their overground sympathisers; and, finally, due
to the relatively subliminal nature of their violence,”
[comments](http://acorn.nationalinterest.in/2010/04/06/the-naxalites-
overreached/) _The Acorn_ while discussing about the escalated violence by the
Naxalites in India.

